args:
The prince once again goes back in time to stop
Aurelius, and once again, Audric bars his way.
While they struggle, Aurelius's body is taken
over by the Other. In order to stop his changed
father, the prince faces off against fiends
summoned by the enemy.
I was just thinking about that man who\ncalled himself Audric. Who could he be?
Does he really know something I don't?\nAm I making a terrible mistake here?
Will you desist in your efforts to travel\nthe chain of causality, then?
Should I really be doing this?\nChanging the very flow of time?
...No. I can't afford to become a prisoner\nto fear and doubt.
Chronos, lend me your power once more.
I am ever here for you, my liege.
Three hundred years ago, my tribe was\nentrusted with watching over the gates\nto all such sealed ruins.
I still waver as to whether or not their\nopening proves my honor or disgrace.

Your answer will be determined by our
results, but worry not—I am certain this
day will long be remembered as the day
which saved our entire kingdom.
It is pretty to think so.
The Sacred Shard rests within. Let us go.
*pant* My father's already gone deep\ninto the ruins!
I told you I would not permit you to\ninterfere, did I not?
Please! If I don't stop my father right now,\nsomething is going to happen that can't\never be undone!
I know this all too well.
And it precisely BECAUSE I know this\nthat I cannot allow you to interfere!
I don't have time for this! If you won't\nmove, I'll force my way through!
Fool! Do you think such a reckless attack\nwill avail you of anything?!
You will either choose to obey me,\nor I will force you to do so!
Hrk! H-he's so strong!\nI'm not going to be able to...
I am pleased to help, but do not rely on\nit overmuch; as I am now, I can do little\nmore than you just saw.
Come on—we need to reach my father\nwhile there's still time.
This is the Sacred Shard\nof these Binding Ruins.
Its power? Most impressive. I can sense\nas much simply by looking at it.
Indeed. This power will prove our\nkingdom's salvation. Let us back to\nto the capital with it at once!
Father, no! Don't touch that Shard!
T-this power... It cannot be... AAAARGH!
Y-Your Majesty? ...Wait. You're not\nHis Majesty, are you?
AAAAH HA HA HA HA! GLORIOUS!
At long last, I am awakened once more!\nI will overrun this land of yours, Alberius,\nand prove to all the depths of your idiocy!
We're too late... Everyone, back away\nfrom my father!
Prince?! What in blazes is going on?!
There's no time to explain. Right now,\nmy father is a danger to us all!
The Sacred Shards were detestable things\nthat restrained me. But now that I have my\nbody, they are nothing.
Heh heh heh... A piece of me is returned!
I am the instrument of your ruin, Other!
Why do you stay my hand?! Do you not\nunderstand this fiend merely wears\nthe face of your father?!
You know who Aurelius truly is right now!
And you know the tragedy that awaits\nshould he be permitted to leave this place!
We must cut out this evil by the root\nhere and now, {player_name}!
Ah, it makes sense to me now.\nYou have cast off the yoke of causality!
And yet, this only proves how great\nmy power truly is!
Perhaps so—but it ends now, when you\nhave but a single piece of yourself!
Aaah ha ha! It's true that my powers\nare but newly awakened...but I have\nmore than my own power in this body!
By the pact, come forth! Grant me power!
Aaaah ha ha ha! Even the power of the six\nloathsome Greatwyrms is mine to wield!\nThis dragonblood is useful indeed...
Zodiark, take hold of your senses!\nThe pact does not bind your heart!
His heart may not be bound by the pact,\nbut so long as I am his master,\nhe will bend the knee to me.
If I cannot control you freely, dragon,\nI can still drive you to madness.
We'll never be able to strike\nwith Zodiark in the way!
Please, Zodiark! Hold yourself back,\nif only for a moment!
He stopped attacking! Now's our chance!
Where did those fiends come from?!
Fools! With three hundred years of miasma\naccumulated, I can create as many fiends\nas I wish!
And while you busy yourself with my\nfriends here, I'll busy myself with\noverrunning this kingdom!
